Name: JK2739
Description:
myo-2::gfp balancer  qIs48
 is an insertion of ccEx9747 with markers: myo-2::GFP expressed brightly
 in the pharynx throughout development, pes-10::GFP expressed in 
embryos, and a gut promoter driving GFP in the  intestine, and is 
homozygous lethal.  Segregates WT glowing hets, non-glowing sterile 
Dpys, very rare homozygous hT2 glowing animals, and dead eggs.   Do not 
distribute this strain;  other labs should request it directly from the 
CGC.   This strain cannot be distributed to commercial organizations.   
This strain cannot be used for any commercial purpose or for work on 
human subjects.  Note: qIs48 has been observed to recombine off hT2, 
typically leaving behind a functional homozygous viable hT2 with Bli-4 
phenotype.

Name: ECA24
Description: ECA19 and DR2078 were crossed to generate a + ttTi5605 Unc4/mIn1 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to ECA20 and wild type males were selected. These males were crossed to ECA23. Wild type hermaphrodites from this cross were selected and selfed over several generations. The selfed animals were then outcrossed to DL238 for eight crossings. The presence of ttTi5605 was monitored by PCR. After 8 out-crossed, ttTi5605-postive animals were then selfed for multiple generations until ttTi5605 was homozygoused. These are animals from plate #1.

Name: ECA25
Description: ECA19 and DR2078 were crossed to generate a + ttTi5605 Unc4/mIn1 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to ECA20 and wild type males were selected. These males were crossed to ECA23. Wild type hermaphrodites from this cross were selected and selfed over several generations. The selfed animals were then outcrossed to DL238 for eight crossings. The presence of ttTi5605 was monitored by PCR using primers oECA28 and oECA29. After 8 rounds of out-crossing, ttTi5605-postive animals were then selfed for multiple generations until ttTi5605 was homozygoused. These are animals from plate #2.

Name: ECA30

Description: ECA17 and DR2078 were crossed to generate a + ttTi5605 Unc4/mIn1 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to ECA16 and wild type males were selected. Name: ECA32
Description: ECA17 and DR2078 were crossed to generate a + ttTi5605 Unc4/mIn1 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to ECA16 and wild type males were selected. Name: ECA33
Description: TJ3000 hermaphrodites and CX11314 males were crossed to generate a zsi3000/CX11314 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to CX11314 hermaphrodites. Eight single pair matings, with one cross progeny male and one CX11314 hermaphrodite were then set up. The presence of zsi3000 was monitored by PCR, using primers oECA468 and oECA469. Cross progeny males from plates that were positive for zsi3000 were outcrossed to CX11314 hermaphrodites for six crossings. After six out-crosses, zsi3000-positive animals were selfed for five generations until zsi3000 was homozygoused.

Name: ECA34
Description: TJ3000 hermaphrodites and DL238 males were crossed to generate a zsi3000/DL238 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to DL238 hermaphrodites. Eight single pair matings were set up with one cross progeny male and one DL238 hermaphrodite. The presence of zsi3000 was monitored by PCR, using primers oECA468 and oECA469. Cross progeny males from plates that were positive for zsi3000 were outcrossed to DL238 hermaphrodites for six crossings. After six rounds of out-crossing, zsi3000-positive animals were selfed for nine generations until zsi3000 was homozygoused.

Name: ECA157
Description:
ECA11 and DR2078 were crossed to generate a + ttTi5605 Unc4/mIn1 strain.
 Males resulting from this cross were crossed to ECA13 and wild type 
males were selected. These males were crossed to ECA23. Wild type 
hermaphrodites from this cross were selected and selfed over several 
generations. The selfed animals were then outcrossed to JU258 for eight 
crossings. The presence of ttTi5605 was monitored by PCR. After 8 
out-crosses, ttTi5605-postive animals were then selfed for multiple 
generations until ttTi5605 was homozygoused. These are animals from 
plate #4.

Cross progeny males from plates that were positive for zsi3000 were outcrossed to MY16 hermaphrodites for six crossings. After six out-crosses, zsi3000-positive animals were selfed for six generations until zsi3000 was homozygoused.

Name: EG6699
Description: oxEx1578 [eft-3p::GFP + Cbr-unc-119]. Pick non-Unc to maintain. Pick Unc to use for injection.   NOTE: New stock received at the CGC 03/21/12. Original stock was reported as no longer segregating Unc. Our copy came from the Morimoto lab. They received the strain around the same time that the stock was sent to the CGC. Therefore, always make sure that the strain segregates Unc before using.

Name: ECA212
Description: TJ3000 hermaphrodites and AB1 males were crossed to generate a zsi3000/AB1 strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to AB1 hermaphrodites. Eight single pair matings, with one cross progeny male and one AB1 hermaphrodite were then set up. Cross progeny males from plates that were positive for zsi3000 were outcrossed to AB1 hermaphrodites for six crossings. After six out-crosses, zsi3000-positive animals were selfed for six generations until zsi3000 was homozygoused. The presence of zsi3000 was monitored by PCR, using primers oECA468 and oECA469. These primers were replaced with oECA29, oECA31 and oECA694 during the selfing stage.

Name: ECA213
Description: TJ3000 hermaphrodites and JT11398 males were crossed to generate a zsi3000/JT11398   strain. Males resulting from this cross were crossed to JT11398   hermaphrodites. Eight single pair matings, with one cross progeny male and one JT11398   hermaphrodite were then set up. Cross progeny males from plates that were positive for zsi3000 were outcrossed to JT11398  hermaphrodites for six crossings. After six out-crosses, zsi3000-positive animals were selfed for six generations until zsi3000 was homozygoused. The presence of zsi3000 was monitored by PCR, using primers oECA468 and oECA469. The primers oECA29, oECA31 and oECA694 were used to confirm the presence of zsi3000 in the homozygous strain.

Name: ECA214
Description: This is a NIL generated by Stefan for the arsenic trioxide peak on chromosome II.   The parental RIAIL was QX103.  Two bulk crosses were followed by 6 backcrosses to CB4856, followed then by 6 selfings to generate the final strain  Genotyping followed the region 6830677 - 8683279 on chromosome II.

Name: ECA215
Description: NIL generated for the left side of the the etoposide interval on chromosome II.  Primers used to genotype the interval oECA605 - oECA608, which primed at 11.64Mb and 11.905Mb   QX103 was used to generate this NIL

Name: ECA216
Description: NIL was generated to span the entire etoposide confidence interval on chromosome II  Primers used to genotype this strain were oECA593 - oECA596, which primed at 11.43Mb and 12.11MB  Starting RIAIL to generate this NIL was QX322

Name: ECA217
Description: NIL was generated to span the entire etoposide confidence interval on chromosome II  Primers used to genotype this strain were oECA593 - oECA596, which primed at 11.43Mb and 12.11MB  Starting RIAIL to generate this NIL was QX462  ** NOTE ** QX462 has the CB4856 genotype across all of chromosome II.

Name: ECA218
Description: This NIL was generated to introgress CB4856 into N2 at the genomic region corresponding to the Arsenic trioxide QTL. Unfortunately, I didn't realize that QX462 was completely CB4856 on chromosome II.  This NIL was generated by crossing QX462 to N2. Two bulk crosses, followed by 6 single pair crosses, followed by 6 single worm selfs.  Primers used to verify the genotype of the crosses were 609 - 612, they primed @ 6.8 and 8.7 Mb.

Name: ECA219
Description: This NIL was generated to introgress the CB4856 genomic region corresponding to the left side of the etoposide QTL confidence interval (11.47 - 12.1 is the CI)  The NIL was generated using QX327 and N2. Two bulk crosses were performed, followed by six single-par back crosses, followed by six single worm selfs.  Primers used to genotype the crosses were 605-608 which primed at 11.64 and 11.9 Mb.

Name: SX1316
Description: mjIs144 [mex-5p::GFP::his-58::21UR-1target::tbb-2 3'UTR] II. piRNA sensor strain. Single copy inserted into ttTi5605 (MosSCI). Name: NL2099
Description: Homozygous rrf-3 deletion allele. Increased sensitivity to RNAi when compared to WT animals. Deletion sequence (deletion in lower case letters, flanking undeleted sequence in capital letters): TGCACATATTctacagaatt ------- --------tacccgattaAATGGACAATT (from Plasterk Lab 11/05).

Name: PD8753
Description: dcr-1 homozygotes are completely sterile. qIs48 is an insertion of ccEx9747 with markers: myo-2::GFP expressed brightly in the pharynx throughout development, pes-10::GFP expressed in embryos, and a gut promoter driving GFP in the intestine, and is homozygous lethal. Segregates WT glowing hets, non-glowing steriles , very rare homozygous hT2 glowing animals, and dead eggs. Do not distribute this strain; other labs should request it directly from the CGC. This strain cannot be distributed to commercial organizations. This strain cannot be used for any commercial purpose or for work on human subjects. Note: qIs48 has been observed to recombine off hT2, typically leaving behind a functional homozygous viable hT2 with Bli-4 phenotype.

Name: PK172
Description: Heterozygotes are WT and segregate WT, paralyzed Dpys, and Uncs which are sterile (with 1-2 escaper progeny). ptc-1 homozygotes have multinucleate germ cells (both sperm and oocytes). ptc-1 homozygotes have an underproliferated germline.

Name: ECA282
Description: EG8899 males and TJ3000 hermaphrodites were crossed to generate a green fluorescent zsi3000 strain. Green fluorescent male offspring from this cross were crossed into hermaphrodite CB1490. Hermaphrodite green fluorescent offspring were allowed to self until homozygoused. The presence of zsi3000 was tested using PCR primers oECA 694 and oECA31; the absence of zsi3000 was tested using PCR primers oECA29 and oECA31. This is the first of two replicates.
